### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### CHECKOUT SAGA — Amount Limit Exceeded (>100.000 TRY)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Login as normal user but checkout with amount > 100.000 TRY
### Payment-service rejects amounts over the limit.
###
### Same compensation flow as payment failure:
###   order.created → inventory.reserve → payment.FAILED (limit)
###   → order.cancelled → inventory.release + notification

### ── 1. Login ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@n11demo.com",
  "password": "User123!"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("access_token", response.body.accessToken);
%}

### ── 2. Checkout with huge amount → triggers limit rejection ────
POST {{host}}/api/orders/checkout
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

{
  "address": "Istanbul, Sisli",
  "items": [
    {
      "productId": 1,
      "productName": "iPhone 15 Pro Max",
      "productPrice": 79999.00,
      "quantity": 2
    }
  ]
}

> {%
  client.global.set("limit_order_id", response.body.id);
  client.log("Limit order ID: " + response.body.id + " — total: 159998 TRY (>100K limit)");
%}

### ── 3. Poll order → should be CANCELLED with limit reason ──────
GET {{host}}/api/orders/{{limit_order_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

> {%
  client.log("Order status: " + response.body.status);
  client.log("Failure reason: " + response.body.failureReason);
%}

### ── 4. Check payment → FAILED with "Limit asildi" ─────────────
GET {{host}}/api/payments/order/{{limit_order_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}
